Class ConcurrentRingBufferRateMeter

  • java.lang.Object
    • stincmale.ratmex.meter.AbstractRateMeter<S,C>
      • stincmale.ratmex.meter.AbstractRingBufferRateMeter<ConcurrentRateMeterStats,ConcurrentRateMeterConfig>
        • stincmale.ratmex.meter.ConcurrentRingBufferRateMeter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Configurable<S>, RateMeter<S>

    @ThreadSafe
public final class ConcurrentRingBufferRateMeter
extends AbstractRingBufferRateMeter<ConcurrentRateMeterStats,ConcurrentRateMeterConfig>
    A thread-safe implementation of AbstractRingBufferRateMeter, which uses AtomikLongArray implementation of LongArray (this might be changed in the future).

      • registerIncorrectlyRegisteredTicksEvent

        protected final void registerIncorrectlyRegisteredTicksEvent​()
        Description copied from class: AbstractRingBufferRateMeter
        This method is called by AbstractRingBufferRateMeter.tick(long, long) not more than once per invocation of AbstractRingBufferRateMeter.tick(long, long) when there is a chance that it might have failed to correctly register ticks. Such a failure can only happen if this object is being used concurrently (see AbstractRingBufferRateMeter(long, Duration, ConcurrentRateMeterConfig, Function, boolean)) and ConcurrentRateMeterConfig.getMode() is false.
        Overrides:
        registerIncorrectlyRegisteredTicksEvent in class AbstractRingBufferRateMeter<ConcurrentRateMeterStats,ConcurrentRateMeterConfig>
